            "type": "text",
            "text": "Aggregate reasoning quality metrics quantify how well a multi-agent system is working \u2014 not just whether it produced an answer, but how confidently, how consistently, and how efficiently. These metrics let you compare debate rounds, tune voting thresholds, detect when agents are failing silently, and justify the cost of multi-agent collaboration against a single-agent baseline."
